@startuml steering_input_to_sas_angle_raw_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Steering Input To SAS Angle Raw Signal Flow\n(steering input + vehicle speed -> SAS angle publication)

participant "Steering input\nmanual/feature steering state" as Steer #F4F7FB
participant "Vehicle state\nVehicleSpeed" as Veh #E8F0FE
participant "SAS\nsteering-angle sensor owner" as SAS #FFF4CC
participant "Chassis observers /\nconsumers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== SAS Inputs ==

Steer -> SAS : frmSteeringStateCanMsg\nor manual steering input
Veh -> SAS : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\nVehicleSpeed
activate SAS
SAS -> SAS : normalize stale steering / vehicle inputs
SAS -> SAS : in manual mode derive steering input\nfrom Chassis::steeringAngle
SAS -> SAS : map steering input to SteeringAngleRaw
note right of SAS
Representative outputs
- SteeringAngleRaw

Representative inputs
- steering input
- vehicle speed
end note

== SAS Publish ==

SAS -> Obs : frmSteeringAngleMsg
SAS -> Obs : traceable raw steering-angle visibility
deactivate SAS

note over Steer, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Steering state arrives from chassis/manual context
2. SAS combines it with vehicle speed
3. SAS derives SteeringAngleRaw
4. Chassis observers consume the raw steering-angle publication
end note

@enduml
